Warcz  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Trąbki Wielkie, within Gdańsk County, Pomeranian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-west of Trąbki Wielkie,  south-west of Pruszcz Gdański, and  south-west of the regional capital Gdańsk.
For details of the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.
